properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 4:02AM CST until January 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...A WINTRY MIX OF PRECIPITATION EXPECTED TODAY...

.A Winter Weather Advisory is in effect for counties in western
Wisconsin north of I-94 for a combination of freezing drizzle and
light snow on Thursday.

A storm system will move from the Central Plains, northeast
across the Upper Midwest by Thursday afternoon. Light
precipitation in the form of mostly freezing drizzle with some
snow mixed in will develop Thursday morning, and continue through
the early afternoon before temperatures rise above freezing. A
light glaze of ice and less than a half inch of snow are likely.
The will cause area roads to become hazardous.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to one half inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Polk, Barron, St. Croix, Dunn and Chippewa Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 3 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
